text: Red River North is a provincial electoral district in the Canadian province of Manitoba that will come into effect at the 2019 Manitoba general election. It will elect one member to the Legislative Assembly of Manitoba. The riding was created by the 2018 provincial redistribution out of parts of Selkirk, St. Paul and a small part of Lac du Bonnet. ==Election results== {| class="wikitable" |- ! colspan="4" | 2016 provincial election redistributed results |- ! bgcolor="#DDDDFF" width="130px" colspan="2" | Party ! bgcolor="#DDDDFF" width="30px" | % |- | | | Progressive Conservative ||align=right| 66.2 |- | | | New Democratic ||align=right| 21.7 |- | | | Liberal ||align=right| 12.1 |} ==References== Category:Manitoba provincial electoral districts
